Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: INFORMATION ON CERTIFIED's NEW TECHNOLOGY "AUGI" CERTIFIED has constructed the Augmented Reality Visual Search Engine (ARVSE), commonly called Augi™, which is a simple way to use a smart device to grant shoppers access to an array of information about products they purchase. Augi™ uses barcode, QRcode, OCR and image recognition to continuously recognize millions of products with seamless transition between product packaging and barcodes all within a live camera view. Additionally, Augi™ utilizes continuous Scan, OCR and Geospatial technology developed by Alphabet (Google Goggles) and IBM. The CERTIFIED Visual Search Technology Team employs this technology to identify and proprietarily analyze products in real-time while simultaneously providing relative information on consumer shopping habits worldwide. CERTIFIED’s Augi™ technology enhances the consumer shopping experience using visual information for search and discovery of products. CERTIFIED designed an Augmented Reality Solution for mobile devices by overlaying relevant information over camera-phone views of the products themselves. Augi™ was initially built to specifically recognize CERTIFIED’s unique Seals as well as the individual objects in smartphone views. However, the technology was expanded to support barcode and QR code recognition on mobile devices for universal application.   Through Augi™, customers gain access to relevant product information for millions of packaged household items such as a box of cereal, milk, toothpaste or other grocery items. Augi™ technology has the capability to track a fisherman’s catch or a farmer’s harvest straight to your table!  This cutting-edge technological advancement is the direct replacement for the invalidated Country of Origin Labeling (COOL) system for beef, pork and chicken in the United States. Augi™ can even notify you if there’s been a product recall as well as provide any emergency health or safety issues specifically related to the product or its ingredients.  For manufacturers and producers, providing consumers the best information about products helps SELL products. Shopping habits can be tracked worldwide which would save marketers millions in researching the decisions on HOW to market a product, WHERE to market the product and TO WHOM the product should be marketed to. For more information on how to leverage this exciting new technology on your products, please contact CERTIFIED, INC.
